import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='count', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend of count over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Count', loc='upper left')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['rate'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of rate?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month

    avg_count_per_month = data.groupby('month')['count'].mean().reset_index()

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='month', y='count', data=avg_count_per_month, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the average count per month?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('Average Count')
    plt.legend(title='Months', loc='upper right', labels=avg_count_per_month['month'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
